		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform2" valign="top" id="forumSubject">
		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Sun, Mar 13th 8:10 PM2005 </span><span class="notbold">| <span class="sm">IP: Logged</span> | <a class="sm" href="/forum.html?forum=1&mid=1110468099644988581&num=36&page=0&post=1&replyto=111076261363273219"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." height="11" width="17" /> Reply to this</a></a> | <a class="sm" href="/db/journal2.html?user=196545"><img border="0" src="/shared/user_journal.gif" border="0" height="12" width="17" /> User's Journal</a>   <a name=111076261363273219></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform2" ><span class="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=196545"><span id="Sage">Friar Reinman</span></a><b><span id="Sage"><br>Sage</span></b><br /><img alt="Avatar" height="93" width="100" src="/uf/Reinman/a100_0022_IMG.jpg"><br /><br /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*"/><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><br />3807 posts
		   <br /><nobr><span class="notbold">Score</span>: Excellent [4.54]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Reinman&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%">
<p><blockquote><b class="sm">Gbaji wrote:</b><hr size="1" />irst off, you're talking about &quot;rounds&quot; of combat. There are no rounds in EQ. It's a pet peeve of mine when people say that as though it has any meaning. Mob attacks have delays just like anything else<hr size="1" /></blockquote> <br /> <br />So when you are talking about &quot;swings&quot;, you are encompassing double/triple attacks, and bash/kick into a single swing.&nbsp;&nbsp;I think that is why people refer to it as a round.  You being a tank should have noticed, especially on slowed mobs that the damage comes in, for lack of a better word, &quot;rounds&quot;.  Is that a fair enough explanation? <br /> <br /><blockquote><b class="sm">Gbaji wrote:</b><hr size="1" />Stuns don't &quot;scale&quot; because they have hard level limits on them. Your ranger's snare spell doesn't have a bit in the description that says &quot;only affects targets up to level 55&quot; in it. Pally stuns do. So your lowest level snare will still have a chance to affect any mob not flagged as unsnarable. My stuns will *not* work on a mob higher then a certain level.  <br /> <br />Ok. They're still really useful, right? But they aren't as useful as they used to be. While stuns are still great, and I'm certainly not complaining, they do not &quot;get more powerful&quot; as we gain levels. They get &quot;weaker&quot; over time. Let me explain.  <br /> <br />Here's the list of paladin stuns (ignoring the early interrupts), with level to use, stun time, and level effect (and a couple relevant notes)  <br /> <br /> <br />Stun                         30     4/55 <br />Holy Might                   49     6/55 damage <br />Force                        52     6/55 damage <br />Force of Akera               53     4/61 <br />Quelious Word of Tranquility 54    10/61 damage,knockback <br /> <br />Force of Akilae              62     4/65 <br />Quelious Word of Serenity    64    10/65 damage,knockback <br />Ancient Force of Chaos       65     4/65 <br /> <br />Force of Piety               66     4/70 <br />Serene Command               68    10/70 damage,knockback <br />Ancient Force of Jeron       70     4/70 <br /> <br /> <br /> <br /> <br />Ok. Look at this list. I've separated it into a few sections. I also bolded the two ancient spells, since those may or may not *ever* end up in your paladin's spell list (they're on a separate line, but I'll discuss that later).  <br /> <br />Here's why I talk about a loss of power. Look at the stuns in the low 50s. We get *4* in like a 5 level period. Additionally, a paladin at level 54 essentially has five stun spells that he can use to affect any mobs up to level 55 (one level higher then he is). Two of his stuns will even affect mobs upwards of 7 levels higher then his own level. That's not too shabby. In fact, most paladins will pick and choose which stuns to load, we have that many. This is literally the &quot;golden levels&quot; for paladin stunning. We can lock down pretty much any mob that we would be likely to ever be tanking. Coincidentally enough, 55 is *also* the cutoff level for pacify, so this is doubly golden in that we're also the best indoor pullers at about this same time period as well.  <br /> <br />Ok. Let's level our paladin through the next set of stuns. As he levels from 54 to 64, he gains two more stuns, but now is much more likely to be fighting mobs that only his higher level stuns affect. He's gained 2 stuns, but lost 3 if he's fighting anything over level 55 (which he will be by level 64 in a group). Also, he's traded in some pretty effective stuns (note the durations on force and holy might) for some less effective ones. The Quellious line is nice, but it's mana expensive, has a knockback *and* a damage component. They're also much slower to cast, so they're harder to use in combat.  <br /> <br />Um... And in many camps you're going to be doing at level 64/65 will have mobs higher then level 61. Golems in PoV are level 62. Everything in BoT is higher then that level. So if you're lucky you've just lost one stun. In most cases, you've lost three stuns, leaving you with only 2 usable stuns in many camps (one of which is less then ideal to use also!). Going from 5 stuns affecting mobs at or near your level to 2 stuns affecting mobs at or near your level is a *huge* reduction in effectiveness.  <br /> <br /> <br />Post 65, the story gets even more grim IMO. There are a ton of 66+ mobs in OoW and DoN. You effectively have now been fully reduced to two stuns, and one of them is the less then desirable damage/knockback/slowcasting/mana-inefficent line. Also remember that every stun upgrade from that point on is not an &quot;extra&quot; stun, but a replacement (they grey out the cast of the lower stun in the line). So even if you are fighting level 65 or lower mobs, and would *like* to have Force of Akera and Force of Piety both loaded up, you still only get one stun. So it's not just that we lose on numbers of stuns against higher level mobs, we don't even gain more stuns to use against mobs lower then us either.  <br /> <br /> <br />Our stunability never approaches the level it was back when we were in our mid 50s. Never. Sure. We're blocking more damage for each second of stun, but that's just damage scale. Everything else scales the same way. Tanks have more AC and HPs. Healers have more efficient heals. Improved focus items add even more. Mobs do more damage in direct relation to the group's abilities to slow/mitigate/heal that damage. Pally stuns don't really gain anything there. Every other class got slows that slow at a higher percentage, and nukes that do more damage, and heals that heal more damage, right? But pallys over those last 10 levels get stuns that reduce the percentage of damage a mob does over time by *less* then they did before. Would you consider a slow with a lower slow percentage an upgrade? Nope. Most wouldn't. But in the case of stuns, we're given the equivalent of a lower value &quot;slow&quot; that's an upgrade because it'll affect mobs of higher level, while the old &quot;better&quot; one didn't. Hmm...  <br /> <br />The absolute best you can do at level 70 is if you have the ancient spell *and* you've spent the AAs for your AA stun (celestial stun IIRC). That brings you up to 4 stuns that affect mobs your level or lower. 2 4 second stuns. 1 &quot;10&quot; second stun, and 1 6 second stun. Contrast to the 2 4s, 2 6s, and one &quot;10&quot; that we had at level 54 (two of which affected mobs *higher* level then us!), and then realize that you had to get an ancient spell and spend AAs to get them, and it's not an increase in power at all. It's a straight relative decrease.  <br /> <br /> <br />Don't get me wrong. I'm not complaining about paladin stuns. They're pretty much the only really unique and useful thing that my class gets. I'm not even that upset about the &quot;upgrade&quot; method used for stuns (I'm mostly pissed that they increased the mana cost on them when they should have decreased it or actually &quot;improved&quot; the spells in some way). I just think that many people seriously overestimate the power of those spells because they don't understand the extreme limitations placed upon them. They don't realize that stuns don't get more powerful as we level, they get less powerful. We can use fewer of them, they have shorter durations, and they cost more mana.<hr size="1" /></blockquote> <br /> <br />A 4 second stun mitigates/avoids proportionate amounts of  damage at level 65 then it does at level 10 and therefore it scales with content.  A 50 hp DD only really &quot;fits&quot; into one level range in the game and therefore does not scale with content.  I hope you can see the difference. <br /> <br /><blockquote><b class="sm">ctrumps wrote:</b><hr size="1" />I agree will Kullayen give rangers better weapons..but on making rangers have the same level nuke/dots as a druid which was said up above ... then why would you need a druid after that? <hr size="1" /></blockquote> <br /> <br />Please quote what you are referring too, if it is to what I said below then read it again, because I never said Rangers should nuke or DoT like Druids. <br /> <br /> <br /></p>
<br /><span class="sm">----------------------------</span><br />Sarcasm, the lowest form of wit, is my best weapon. <br /> <br /><a href="HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=596992" title="HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=596992" target="akztarg">Reinmon</a>, <span class="sm">58 Ranger</span> <br /> <a href="HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=758729" title="HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=758729" target="akztarg">Slaher</a>, <span class="sm">58 Shaman</span> <br /><a href="HTTP://www.guildportal.com/Guild.aspx?GuildID=15391&TabID=129880 " title="HTTP://www.guildportal.com/Guild.aspx?GuildID=15391&TabID=129880 " target="akztarg">Aude Sapere</a> <br />Povar Server</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8">Posting from the thin edge of the wedge.</td></tr></table>
